1
00:00:02,250 --> 00:00:03,870
-: Now we have to pass some data

2
00:00:03,870 --> 00:00:06,600
from our controller to our view.

3
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:08,910
And for that, we have multiple items,

4
00:00:08,910 --> 00:00:12,240
or multiple routes, that are available.

5
00:00:12,240 --> 00:00:14,820
First one here is a ViewBag.

6
00:00:14,820 --> 00:00:18,630
ViewBag transfers data from controller to view,

7
00:00:18,630 --> 00:00:20,760
and not vice versa.

8
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:23,040
And that is exactly what we want.

9
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:25,950
We want to pass the data that we have in our controller

10
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:27,240
to our view,

11
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,910
and it is ideal for a situation

12
00:00:29,910 --> 00:00:33,183
in which the temporary data is not in a model.

13
00:00:34,170 --> 00:00:37,380
Like in our example, we need the dropdown list,

14
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:39,930
and that is not within our model.

15
00:00:39,930 --> 00:00:42,870
We do not have a property to store that.

16
00:00:42,870 --> 00:00:46,260
So in that case, we can store this in a ViewBag,

17
00:00:46,260 --> 00:00:48,363
and pass that to our view.

18
00:00:50,910 --> 00:00:54,600
ViewBag is a dynamic property that takes advantage

19
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:59,460
of the new dynamic features in C# 4.0.

20
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:01,770
Any number of properties and values

21
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:04,050
can be assigned to a ViewBag,

22
00:01:04,050 --> 00:01:06,930
and the ViewBag's life only exists

23
00:01:06,930 --> 00:01:10,170
during the current HTTP request.

24
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:14,400
ViewBag values will be null if there is any redirection.

25
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,570
Like in our case,

26
00:01:15,570 --> 00:01:18,870
we will be passing the value from controller to view,

27
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:21,240
and we will not be redirecting,

28
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:24,093
that is why the ViewBag value will persist.

29
00:01:25,530 --> 00:01:27,360
Last point is that ViewBag

30
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:29,823
is actually a wrapper around ViewData.

31
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:33,630
Now, you might think, "What is ViewData?"

32
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:37,080
But we will cover one thing at a time.

33
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:38,700
First, let me switch back

34
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:41,463
and show you how we can use ViewBag.

35
00:01:42,540 --> 00:01:44,130
Right here in the code,

36
00:01:44,130 --> 00:01:46,470
we are getting all the category list,

37
00:01:46,470 --> 00:01:49,470
but I am inside the Index action.

38
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:50,790
Let me cut this.

39
00:01:50,790 --> 00:01:54,303
We actually need that inside the Create action.

40
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:58,200
So right here, let me paste that here.

41
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,640
And now, you might be thinking

42
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,920
that we are not passing anything here.

43
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:04,950
Why don't we pass the category list?

44
00:02:04,950 --> 00:02:06,690
But if I go to the view,

45
00:02:06,690 --> 00:02:09,449
you can see we have defined a model at the top,

46
00:02:09,449 --> 00:02:11,103
which is the Product model.

47
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:16,110
So now we need to pass this category list to our view,

48
00:02:16,110 --> 00:02:19,110
and we want to use ViewBag.

49
00:02:19,110 --> 00:02:22,440
So far that we can say ViewBag.CategoryList

50
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,397
is equal to CategoryList.

51
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:27,600
We can give any name that we want,

52
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,790
and this name that we give here

53
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:32,430
will basically act as a key value,

54
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:34,680
where key will be CategoryList,

55
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,593
and value will be whatever we assign here.

56
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:42,180
Once we add this here, then inside the create

57
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:45,513
we can fetch that and display that in a dropdown.

58
00:02:46,620 --> 00:02:51,000
Let me scroll down, and there we have the Price100,

59
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,450
after that let me copy and paste it one more time.

60
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:57,750
The label will be for CategoryId,

61
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:01,620
ASP validation, we can change that to be CategoryId,

62
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:04,800
but here, we want the select field.

63
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,830
Now when we are using select rather than input,

64
00:03:07,830 --> 00:03:10,230
we cannot use the self-closing tag.

65
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:13,050
We have to explicitly close that.

66
00:03:13,050 --> 00:03:17,190
And after that, I will add one more default option here,

67
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:21,090
which will be disabled selected by default,

68
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:25,287
and there we will display "Select Category."

69
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,110
Now asp-for, we have that as CategoryId,

70
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:35,130
but we need to display all the items in the dropdown.

71
00:03:35,130 --> 00:03:38,910
For that we have a special tag helper, asp-items,

72
00:03:38,910 --> 00:03:43,910
and this expects an IEnumerable of select list item.

73
00:03:44,070 --> 00:03:48,060
We have that in our ViewBag, so in order to extract that

74
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:52,680
we will write, ViewBag, dot, and we need the key name.

75
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,570
Now key name, if you write here,

76
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:56,970
it will not help with IntelliSense,

77
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:59,070
because it is not dynamic.

78
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:01,200
You can give any key name here,

79
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:04,200
and IntelliSense cannot detect what you gave,

80
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:08,340
so you have to type that and make sure that it matches.

81
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:10,290
If there is any spelling mistake,

82
00:04:10,290 --> 00:04:11,673
things will not work.

83
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,433
For the class here,

84
00:04:13,433 --> 00:04:17,130
we will give it a Bootstrap class of form-select,

85
00:04:17,130 --> 00:04:20,192
and with that, let me run the application.

86
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:24,990
We go to Product here,

87
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:27,930
and we will have to go to Create New Product,

88
00:04:27,930 --> 00:04:30,180
scroll down, perfect.

89
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:32,130
We have Select Category,

90
00:04:32,130 --> 00:04:35,673
and there we have Action, SciFi, and History.

91
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:40,353
So our dropdown is looking great with Create Product.

92
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:45,870
Now that is one way of doing things with ViewBag.

93
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:49,110
Let me continue and show you the alternative

94
00:04:49,110 --> 00:04:50,463
in the next video.

